videos.description: Emmitt Williams throws down the monster jam getting the LSU crowd on their feet.

videos.headline: Williams gets the crowd going early with the dunk

videos.description: Nick Richards finds himself wide open for the easy putback jam.

videos.headline: Richards gets the easy putback dunk

videos.description: Javonte Smart goes down the lane and gets the floater off the glass to fall over a couple defenders.

videos.description: Nate Sestina gets the block, which leads to Tyrese Maxey finishing with the layup plus the foul.

videos.headline: Sestina's block leads to the Maxey and-1

videos.description: Kentucky big man Nate Sestina drains back-to-back 3-pointers giving the Wildcats a 15-point lead over LSU.

tracking.trackingName: NCB_One-Play (Sestina's back-to-back 3's force an LSU timeout) 2020/02/18

videos.headline: Sestina's back-to-back 3's force an LSU timeout

videos.description: Kentucky center Nick Richards throws down the dunk, but lands on the ball and turns his ankle. He returned to the game a couple minutes later.

tracking.trackingName: NCB_One-Play (Richards rolls his ankle on the ball after big dunk 2020/02/18

videos.headline: Richards rolls his ankle on the ball after big dunk

videos.description: Immanuel Quickley goes for a team-high 21 points while Ashton Hagans chips in 11 to help Kentucky take down LSU 79-76.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCB Highlight (Quickley and Hagans come up big in Kentucky’s win) 2020/02/18 ESHEET SOTFULL
